45/Britain-in-a-day-the-longest-train-route-in-the-country.html |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |access-date=3 December 2015 }}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== North America ===\n\n==== Canada ====\n<!--- Please add \"Operator\" column only if there different operators. --->\nAll services are operated by [[Via Rail]].\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width= align=\n|+ \n! Origin City\n! Destination City\n! Train Name/No\n! Distance\n! No.of Stops\n! Frequency\n! data-sort-type=\"number\"|Scheduled running time\n|-\n| [[Union Station (Toronto)|Toronto]] \n| [[Pacific Central Station (Vancouver)|Vancouver]] \n| [[The Canadian]] 1 / 2\n| 4466&nbsp;km\n| 66\n| Tri-weekly\n| 86 h (3.5 days)\n|-\n| [[Union Station (Winnipeg)|Winnipeg]]\n| [[Churchill station (Manitoba)|Churchill]]\n| [[Winnipeg\u2013Churchill train|693 / 692]]\n| 1710&nbsp;km\n| 53\n| Bi-weekly\n| 36 h (2 days)\n|-\n| [[Central Station (Montreal)|Montreal]] \n| [[Halifax (Nova Scotia)|Halifax]] \n| [[Ocean (train)|The Ocean]] 14 / 15\n| 1346&nbsp;km\n| 25\n| Tri-weekly\n| 23 h 43 mins (1 day)\n|-\n|[[Jasper, Alberta|Jasper]]\n|[[Prince Rupert, British Columbia|Prince Rupert]]\n|[[Jasper\u2013Prince Rupert train|5 / 6]]\n|1160&nbsp;km\n|32\n|Tri-weekly\n|33 h 40 mins (2 days)\n|}\n\n==== United States ====\n<!--- Please add \"Operator Name\" column only if there different operators. --->\nAll services are run by [[Amtrak]].\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width= align=\n|+ \n! Origin City\n! Destination City\n! Train Name/No\n! Distance\n! No.of Stops\n! Frequency\n! data-sort-type=\"number\"|Scheduled running time\n!{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| [[Chicago Union Station|Chicago]]\n| [[Union Station (Los Angeles)|Los Angeles]]\n| [[Texas Eagle]] 421 / 422\n| 4390&nbsp;km\n| 40\n| Tri-weekly\n| 65 hrs 20 mins (~3 days)\n|<ref name=\"amtrak.com \u2013 Texas Eagle\" />\n|-\n| [[Emeryville station (Amtrak)|Emeryville]] \n| [[Chicago Union Station|Chicago]]\n| [[California Zephyr]] 5 / 6\n| 3924&nbsp;km\n| 32\n| Daily\n| 